1-81f1ba469547\",\"version\":\"2.1.63\",\"gitBranch\":\"alisha/kiro-oneshot\",\"slug\":\"glittery-waddling-parrot\",\"type\":\"progress\",\"data\":{\"type\":\"hook_progress\",\"hookEvent\":\"PostToolUse\",\"hookName\":\"PostToolUse:Read\",\"command\":\"callback\"},\"parentToolUseID\":\"toolu_01PAoZ5e8Zq3owv3YvipCA82\",\"toolUseID\":\"toolu_01PAoZ5e8Zq3owv3YvipCA82\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-03-03T19:41:20.052Z\",\"uuid\":\"d21c7181-ed7f-470b-a2a1-c2da93fa6e95\"}\n{\"parentUuid\":\"89082276-6c33-43e9-9bc9-c2887e20a694\",\"isSidechain\":false,\"userType\":\"external\",\"cwd\":\"/Users/alisha/Projects/wt/kiro-oneshot\",\"sessionId\":\"f99ad6f8-76a8-4008-9fe1-81f1ba469547\",\"version\":\"2.1.63\",\"gitBranch\":\"alisha/kiro-oneshot\",\"slug\":\"glittery-waddling-parrot\",\"type\":\"user\",\"message\":{\"role\":\"user\",\"content\":[{\"tool_use_id\":\"toolu_01PAoZ5e8Zq3owv3YvipCA82\",\"type\":\"tool_result\",\"content\":\"     1→# Kiro Agent Integration\\n     2→\\n     3→Implementation one-pager for the Kiro (Amazon AI coding CLI) agent integration.\\n     4→\\n     5→## Identity\\n     6→\\n     7→| Field | Value |\\n     8→|-------|-------|\\n     9→| Package | `kiro` |\\n    10→| Registry Key | `kiro` |\\n    11→| Agent Type | `Kiro` |\\n    12→| Binary | `kiro-cli` |\\n    13→| Preview | Yes |\\n    14→| Protected Dir | `.kiro` |\\n    15→\\n    16→## Hook Events (5 total)\\n    17→\\n    18→| Kiro Hook (camelCase) | CLI Subcommand (kebab-case) | EventType | Notes |\\n    19→|----------------------|----------------------------|-----------|-------|\\n    20→| `agentSpawn` | `agent-spawn` | `SessionStart` | Agent initializes |\\n    21→| `userPromptSubmit` | `user-prompt-submit` | `TurnStart` | stdin includes `prompt` field |\\n    22→| `preToolUse` | `pre-tool-use` | `nil, nil` | Pass-through |\\n    23→| `postToolUse` | `post-tool-use` | `nil, nil` | Pass-through |\\n    24→| `stop` | `stop` | `TurnEnd` | Checkpoint trigger |\\n    25→\\n    26→No `SessionEnd` hook exists — sessions end implicitly (similar to Cursor).\\n    27→\\n    28→## Hook Configuration\\n    29→\\n    30→**File:** `.kiro/agents/entire.json`\\n    31→\\n    32→We own the entire file — no round-trip preservation needed (unlike Cursor's shared `hooks.json`).\\n    33→\\n    34→**Format:**\\n    35→```json\\n    36→{\\n    37→  \\\"name\\\": \\\"entire\\\",\\n    38→  \\\"tools\\\": [\\\"read\\\", \\\"write\\\", \\\"shell\\\", \\\"grep\\\", \\\"glob\\\", \\\"aws\\\", \\\"report\\\",\\n    39→            \\\"introspect\\\", \\\"knowledge\\\", \\\"thinking\\\", \\\"todo\\\", \\\"delegate\\\"],\\n    40→  \\\"hooks\\\": {\\n    41→    \\\"agentSpawn\\\": [{\\\"command\\\": \\\"entire hooks kiro agent-spawn\\\"}],\\n    42→    \\\"userPromptSubmit\\\": [{\\\"command\\\": \\\"entire hooks kiro user-prompt-submit\\\"}],\\n    43→    \\\"preToolUse\\\": [{\\\"command\\\": \\\"entire hooks kiro pre-tool-use\\\"}],\\n    44→    \\\"postToolUse\\\": [{\\\"command\\\": \\\"entire hooks kiro post-tool-use\\\"}],\\n    45→    \\\"stop\\\": [{\\\"command\\\": \\\"entire hooks kiro stop\\\"}]\\n    46→  }\\n    47→}\\n    48→```\\n    49→\\n    50→Note: The file is a Kiro agent definition. Hooks must be nested under the `hooks` field.\\n    51→Required top-level fields: `name`. Optional: `$schema`, `description`, `prompt`, `mcpServers`,\\n    52→`tools`, `toolAliases`, `allowedTools`, `resources`, `hooks`, `toolsSettings`, `model`, etc.\\n    53→\\n    54→**Important:** The `tools` array must include all default Kiro tools. Without it, `--agent entire`\\n    55→restricts the model to zero tools. The tool names come from `~/.kiro/agents/agent_config.json.example`.\\n    56→\\n    57→## Agent Activation\\n    58→\\n    59→Hooks only fire when `--agent entire` is passed to `kiro-cli chat`. Without this flag,\\n    60→`.kiro/agents/entire.json` is not loaded and hooks do not execute.\\n    61→\\n    62→**`--no-interactive` mode:** Does not fire agent hooks. All E2E tests use interactive (tmux) mode.\\n    63→\\n    64→**TUI prompt indicator:** `!>` in trust-all mode (with `-a` flag). The `Credits:` line\\n    65→appears after each agent response and serves as a reliable completion marker.\\n    66→\\n    67→## Hook Stdin Format\\n    68→\\n    69→All hooks receive the same JSON structure on stdin:\\n    70→```json\\n    71→{\\n    72→  \\\"hook_event_name\\\": \\\"userPromptSubmit\\\",\\n    73→  \\\"cwd\\\": \\\"/path/to/repo\\\",\\n    74→  \\\"prompt\\\": \\\"user message\\\",\\n    75→  \\\"tool_name\\\": \\\"fs_write\\\",\\n    76→  \\\"tool_input\\\": \\\"...\\\",\\n    77→  \\\"tool_response\\\": \\\"...\\\"\\n    78→}\\n    79→```\\n    80→\\n    81→Fields are populated based on the hook event — `prompt` only for `userPromptSubmit`, tool fields only for tool hooks.\\n    82→\\n    83→## Transcript Storage\\n    84→\\n    85→**Source:** SQLite database at `~/Library/Application Support/kiro-cli/data.sqlite3` (macOS)\\n    86→or `~/.local/share/kiro-cli/data.sqlite3` (Linux).\\n    87→\\n    88→**Table:** `conversations_v2`\\n    89→- `key` column: CWD path (used for lookup)\\n    90→- `value` column: JSON blob with conversation data\\n    91→- `updated_at` column: timestamp for ordering\\n    92→\\n    93→**Conversation JSON structure:**\\n    94→```json\\n    95→{\\n    96→  \\\"conversation_id\\\": \\\"uuid-v4\\\",\\n    97→  \\\"history\\\": [\\n    98→    {\\\"role\\\": \\\"user\\\", \\\"content\\\": [{\\\"type\\\": \\\"text\\\", \\\"text\\\": \\\"...\\\"}]},\\n    99→    {\\\"role\\\": \\\"assistant\\\", \\\"content\\\": [{\\\"type\\\": \\\"text\\\", \\\"text\\\": \\\"...\\\"}, {\\\"type\\\": \\\"tool_use\\\", \\\"name\\\": \\\"fs_write\\\", \\\"input\\\": {...}}]},\\n   100→    {\\\"role\\\": \\\"request_metadata\\\", \\\"input_tokens\\\": 150, \\\"output_tokens\\\": 80}\\n   101→  ]\\n   102→}\\n   103→```\\n   104→\\n   105→## Session ID Discovery\\n   106→\\n   107→Hook stdin does not include session ID. We query SQLite by CWD:\\n   108→```sql\\n   109→SELECT json_extract(value, '$.conversation_id')\\n   110→FROM conversations_v2\\n   111→WHERE key = '<cwd>'\\n   112→ORDER BY updated_at DESC LIMIT 1\\n   113→```\\n   114→\\n   115→## SQLite Access Strategy\\n   116→\\n   117→Uses `sqlite3` CLI (pre-installed on macOS/Linux) rather than a Go library to avoid CGO dependencies. Same approach as OpenCode's `opencode export` CLI.\\n   118→\\n   119→**Test mock:** `ENTIRE_TEST_KIRO_MOCK_DB=1` env var causes the agent to skip SQLite queries and use pre-written mock files.\\n   120→\\n   121→## File Modification Tools\\n   122→\\n   123→Tools that modify files on disk:\\n   124→- `fs_write` — write file content\\n   125→- `str_replace` — string replacement in files\\n   126→- `create_file` — create new files\\n   127→- `write_file` — write/overwrite files\\n   128→- `edit_file` — edit existing files\\n   129→\\n   130→## Caching\\n   131→\\n   132→Transcript data is cached to `.entire/tmp/<sessionID>.json` (same pattern as OpenCode).\\n   133→\"}]},\"uuid\":\"b6db1406-3024-4bf0-a6f5-b13f20096eae\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-03-03T19:41:20.051Z\",\"toolUseResult\":{\"type\":\"text\",\"file\":{\"filePath\":\"/Users/alisha/Projects/wt/kiro-oneshot/cmd/entire/cli/agent/kiro/AGENT.md\",\"content\":\"# Kiro Agent Integration\\n\\nImplementation one-pager for the Kiro (Amazon AI coding CLI) agent integration.\\n\\n## Identity\\n\\n| Field | Value |\\n|-------|-------|\\n| Package | `kiro` |\\n| Registry Key | `kiro` |\\n| Agent Type | `Kiro` |\\n| Binary | `kiro-cli` |\\n| Preview | Yes |\\n| Protected Dir | `.kiro` |\\n\\n## Hook Events (5 total)\\n\\n| Kiro Hook (camelCase) | CLI Subcommand (kebab-case) | EventType | Notes |\\n|----------------------|----------------------------|-----------|-------|\\n| `agentSpawn` | `agent-spawn` | `SessionStart` | Agent initializes |\\n| `userPromptSubmit` | `user-prompt-submit` | `TurnStart` | stdin includes `prompt` field |\\n| `preToolUse` | `pre-tool-use` | `nil, nil` | Pass-through |\\n| `postToolUse` | `post-tool-use` | `nil, nil` | Pass-through |\\n| `stop` | `stop` | `TurnEnd` | Checkpoint trigger |\\n\\nNo `SessionEnd` hook exists — sessions end implicitly (similar to Cursor).\\n\\n## Hook Configuration\\n\\n**File:** `.kiro/agents/entire.json`\\n\\nWe own the entire file — no round-trip preservation needed (unlike Cursor's shared `hooks.json`).\\n\\n**Format:**\\n```json\\n{\\n  \\\"name\\\": \\\"entire\\\",\\n  \\\"tools\\\": [\\\"read\\\", \\\"write\\\", \\\"shell\\\", \\\"grep\\\", \\\"glob\\\", \\\"aws\\\", \\\"report\\\",\\n            \\\"introspect\\\", \\\"knowledge\\\", \\\"thinking\\\", \\\"todo\\\", \\\"delegate\\\"],\\n  \\\"hooks\\\": {\\n    \\\"agentSpawn\\\": [{\\\"command\\\": \\\"entire hooks kiro agent-spawn\\\"}],\\n    \\\"userPromptSubmit\\\": [{\\\"command\\\": \\\"entire hooks kiro user-prompt-submit\\\"}],\\n    \\\"preToolUse\\\": [{\\\"command\\\": \\\"entire hooks kiro pre-tool-use\\\"}],\\n    \\\"postToolUse\\\": [{\\\"command\\\": \\\"entire hooks kiro post-tool-use\\\"}],\\n    \\\"stop\\\": [{\\\"command\\\": \\\"entire hooks kiro stop\\\"}]\\n  }\\n}\\n```\\n\\nNote: The file is a Kiro agent definition. Hooks must be nested under the `hooks` field.\\nRequired top-level fields: `name`. Optional: `$schema`, `description`, `prompt`, `mcpServers`,\\n`tools`, `toolAliases`, `allowedTools`, `resources`, `hooks`, `toolsSettings`, `model`, etc.\\n\\n**Important:** The `tools` array must include all default Kiro tools. Without it, `--agent entire`\\nrestricts the model to zero tools. The tool names come from `~/.kiro/agents/agent_config.json.example`.\\n\\n## Agent Activation\\n\\nHooks only fire when `--agent entire` is passed to `kiro-cli chat`. Without this flag,\\n`.kiro/agents/entire.json` is not loaded and hooks do not execute.\\n\\n**`--no-interactive` mode:** Does not fire agent hooks. All E2E tests use interactive (tmux) mode.\\n\\n**TUI prompt indicator:** `!>` in trust-all mode (with 