ut **not** for the Kiro IDE (VS Code extension), which reads hooks from `.kiro/hooks/*.kiro.hook` files. We need to install IDE hooks there while keeping the existing CLI agent hooks.\\n     6→\\n     7→Key difference: CLI hooks receive JSON on stdin. IDE hooks pass data via environment variables (`USER_PROMPT` for promptSubmit) with **no stdin**. The lifecycle parsers must handle empty stdin gracefully.\\n     8→\\n     9→## Changes\\n    10→\\n    11→### 1. `cmd/entire/cli/agent/kiro/types.go` — Add IDE hook types\\n    12→\\n    13→Add 3 structs for the `.kiro.hook` file format:\\n    14→\\n    15→```go\\n    16→type kiroIDEHookFile struct {\\n    17→    Enabled     bool            `json:\\\"enabled\\\"`\\n    18→    Name        string          `json:\\\"name\\\"`\\n    19→    Description string          `json:\\\"description\\\"`\\n    20→    Version     string          `json:\\\"version\\\"`\\n    21→    When        kiroIDEHookWhen `json:\\\"when\\\"`\\n    22→    Then        kiroIDEHookThen `json:\\\"then\\\"`\\n    23→}\\n    24→\\n    25→type kiroIDEHookWhen struct {\\n    26→    Type string `json:\\\"type\\\"`\\n    27→}\\n    28→\\n    29→type kiroIDEHookThen struct {\\n    30→    Type    string `json:\\\"type\\\"`\\n    31→    Command string `json:\\\"command\\\"`\\n    32→}\\n    33→```\\n    34→\\n    35→### 2. `cmd/entire/cli/agent/kiro/hooks.go` — Install/uninstall/check IDE hooks\\n    36→\\n    37→**New constants and data:**\\n    38→- `ideHooksDir = \\\"hooks\\\"` — directory within `.kiro`\\n    39→- `ideHookFileSuffix = \\\".kiro.hook\\\"`\\n    40→- `ideHookDefs` — slice of 4 definitions mapping filename → trigger type → CLI verb\\n    41→\\n    42→**IDE hooks to install (4 files):**\\n    43→\\n    44→| File | `when.type` | Command |\\n    45→|------|-------------|---------|\\n    46→| `entire-prompt-submit.kiro.hook` | `promptSubmit` | `entire hooks kiro user-prompt-submit` |\\n    47→| `entire-stop.kiro.hook` | `agentStop` | `entire hooks kiro stop` |\\n    48→| `entire-pre-tool-use.kiro.hook` | `preToolUse` | `entire hooks kiro pre-tool-use` |\\n    49→| `entire-post-tool-use.kiro.hook` | `postToolUse` | `entire hooks kiro post-tool-use` |\\n    50→\\n    51→No `agentSpawn` IDE hook (no IDE trigger exists). First `promptSubmit` serves as session start.\\n    52→\\n    53→**Modified functions:**\\n    54→- `InstallHooks`: After writing CLI agent file, also call `installIDEHooks()` to create 4 `.kiro.hook` files. Idempotency gate checks both CLI and IDE hooks. Returns 9 on fresh install (5 CLI + 4 IDE).\\n    55→- `UninstallHooks`: Also remove the 4 IDE hook files (idempotent, no error if missing).\\n    56→- `AreHooksInstalled`: Also check for IDE hook files — returns true if EITHER CLI or IDE hooks are present.\\n    57→\\n    58→**New helpers:**\\n    59→- `installIDEHooks(worktreeRoot, cmdPrefix) (int, error)` — creates `.kiro/hooks/` dir and writes 4 files\\n    60→- `allIDEHooksPresent(worktreeRoot string, localDev bool) bool` — checks all 4 IDE hook files exist and have correct commands\\n    61→- `isEntireIDEHook(hook kiroIDEHookFile) bool` — checks if IDE hook belongs to Entire\\n    62→\\n    63→### 3. `cmd/entire/cli/agent/kiro/lifecycle.go` — Handle empty stdin (IDE mode)\\n    64→\\n    65→Add a local helper `readHookInputOrEmpty(stdin)` that wraps `ReadAndParseHookInput` and returns a zero-value `hookInputRaw{}` on empty stdin (instead of erroring). Malformed JSON still returns errors.\\n    66→\\n    67→**Modified parsers:**\\n    68→- `parseAgentSpawn`: Use `readHookInputOrEmpty`. Empty stdin is fine — just generates session ID.\\n    69→- `parseUserPromptSubmit`: Use `readHookInputOrEmpty`. If `raw.Prompt` is empty, read `os.Getenv(\\\"USER_PROMPT\\\")`. If `raw.CWD` is empty, use `paths.WorktreeRoot(ctx)`.\\n    70→- `parseStop`: Use `readHookInputOrEmpty`. If `raw.CWD` is empty, use `paths.WorktreeRoot(ctx)`.\\n    71→\\n    72→Note: `paths.WorktreeRoot(ctx)` used for CWD fallback (not