ok(hook kiroIDEHookFile) bool` — checks if IDE hook belongs to Entire\\n\\n### 3. `cmd/entire/cli/agent/kiro/lifecycle.go` — Handle empty stdin (IDE mode)\\n\\nAdd a local helper `readHookInputOrEmpty(stdin)` that wraps `ReadAndParseHookInput` and returns a zero-value `hookInputRaw{}` on empty stdin (instead of erroring). Malformed JSON still returns errors.\\n\\n**Modified parsers:**\\n- `parseAgentSpawn`: Use `readHookInputOrEmpty`. Empty stdin is fine — just generates session ID.\\n- `parseUserPromptSubmit`: Use `readHookInputOrEmpty`. If `raw.Prompt` is empty, read `os.Getenv(\\\"USER_PROMPT\\\")`. If `raw.CWD` is empty, use `paths.WorktreeRoot(ctx)`.\\n- `parseStop`: Use `readHookInputOrEmpty`. If `raw.CWD` is empty, use `paths.WorktreeRoot(ctx)`.\\n\\nNote: `paths.WorktreeRoot(ctx)` used for CWD fallback (not `os.Getwd()` which is forbidden by linter).\\n\\n### 4. `cmd/entire/cli/agent/kiro/hooks_test.go` — Update and add tests\\n\\n**Updated existing tests** (count changes from 5 → 9):\\n- `TestInstallHooks_FreshInstall`: expect count 9\\n- `TestInstallHooks_LocalDevMode`: expect count 9\\n- `TestInstallHooks_Idempotent`: first count = 9\\n- `TestInstallHooks_ForceReinstall`: expect count 9\\n- `TestInstallHooks_CountMatchesHookNames`: update to assert `count == len(ag.HookNames()) + len(ideHookDefs)`\\n\\n**New tests:**\\n- `TestInstallHooks_CreatesIDEHookFiles` — verify all 4 files exist\\n- `TestInstallHooks_IDEHooksValidJSON` — verify JSON structure, enabled, version, when.type, then.type, command\\n- `TestInstallHooks_IDEHooksLocalDevMode` — verify local dev command prefix\\n- `TestInstallHooks_IDEHooksFilePermissions` — verify 0600\\n- `TestInstallHooks_IDEHooksAllTriggerTypes` — verify each file has correct when.type\\n- `TestUninstallHooks_RemovesIDEHookFiles` — verify cleanup\\n- `TestAreHooksInstalled_IDEOnlyHooks` — verify detection without CLI agent file\\n- `TestInstallHooks_Idempotent_IncludesIDEHooks` — verify combined idempotency\\n\\n### 5. `