\",\"id\":\"toolu_01G1i7s5jeg4tutPay14n1Lf\",\"name\":\"Read\",\"input\":{\"file_path\":\"/Users/alisha/Projects/wt/kiro-oneshot/cmd/entire/cli/hook_registry.go\"},\"caller\":{\"type\":\"direct\"}}],\"stop_reason\":null,\"stop_sequence\":null,\"usage\":{\"input_tokens\":1,\"cache_creation_input_tokens\":4371,\"cache_read_input_tokens\":55856,\"cache_creation\":{\"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens\":0,\"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens\":4371},\"output_tokens\":4,\"service_tier\":\"standard\",\"inference_geo\":\"not_available\"},\"context_management\":null},\"requestId\":\"req_011CYgm53QpiQ48fZqdFnBUn\",\"uuid\":\"c46bf569-00d9-4a89-b373-725e3eec8ef0\"},\"normalizedMessages\":[],\"type\":\"agent_progress\",\"prompt\":\"\",\"agentId\":\"ad3c9b2e11cd3a9aa\"},\"toolUseID\":\"agent_msg_01Hae6tBjtF6M39zkiWyFieq\",\"parentToolUseID\":\"toolu_01Qf7tecwL49faBn75P6zcYS\",\"uuid\":\"d8d26cad-4a68-486e-bc88-5dd42660a2c9\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-03-03T20:15:18.767Z\"}\n{\"parentUuid\":\"d8d26cad-4a68-486e-bc88-5dd42660a2c9\",\"isSidechain\":false,\"userType\":\"external\",\"cwd\":\"/Users/alisha/Projects/wt/kiro-oneshot\",\"sessionId\":\"f99ad6f8-76a8-4008-9fe1-81f1ba469547\",\"version\":\"2.1.63\",\"gitBranch\":\"alisha/kiro-oneshot\",\"slug\":\"glittery-waddling-parrot\",\"type\":\"progress\",\"data\":{\"message\":{\"type\":\"user\",\"message\":{\"role\":\"user\",\"content\":[{\"tool_use_id\":\"toolu_01PG3KqsXQhmoNV2eAyFsDrr\",\"type\":\"tool_result\",\"content\":\"     1→# Entire - CLI\\n     2→\\n     3→This repo contains the CLI for Entire.\\n     4→\\n     5→## Architecture\\n     6→\\n     7→- CLI built with github.com/spf13/cobra and github.com/charmbracelet/huh\\n     8→\\n     9→## Key Directories\\n    10→\\n    11→### Commands (`cmd/`)\\n    12→\\n    13→- `entire/`: Main CLI entry point\\n    14→- `entire/cli`: CLI utilities and helpers\\n    15→- `entire/cli/commands`: actual command implementations\\n    16→- `entire/cli/agent`: agent implementations (Claude Code, Gemini CLI, OpenCode, Cursor) - see [Agent Integration Checklist](docs/architecture/agent-integration-checklist.md) and [Agent Implementation Guide](docs/architecture/agent-guide.md)\\n    17→- `entire/cli/strategy`: strategy implementation (manual-commit) - see section below\\n    18→- `entire/cli/checkpoint`: checkpoint storage abstractions (temporary and committed)\\n    19→- `entire/cli/session`: session state management\\n    20→- `entire/cli/integration_test`: integration tests (simulated hooks)\\n    21→- `e2e/`: E2E tests with real agent calls (see [e2e/README.md](e2e/README.md))\\n    22→\\n    23→## Tech Stack\\n    24→\\n    25→- Language: Go 1.25.x\\n    26→- Build tool: mise, go modules\\n    27→- Linting: golangci-lint\\n    28→\\n    29→## Development\\n    30→\\n    31→### Running Tests\\n    32→\\n    33→```bash\\n    34→mise run test\\n    35→```\\n    36→\\n    37→### Running Integration Tests\\n    38→\\n    39→```bash\\n    40→mise run test:integration\\n    41→```\\n    42→\\n    43→### Running All Tests (CI)\\n    44→\\n    45→```bash\\n    46→mise run test:ci\\n    47→```\\n    48→\\n    49→Integration tests use the `//go:build integration` build tag and are located in `cmd/entire/cli/integration_test/`.\\n    50→\\n    51→### Running E2E Tests (Only When Explicitly Requested)\\n    52→\\n    53→**IMPORTANT: Do NOT run E2E tests proactively.** E2E tests make real API calls to agents, which consume tokens and cost money. Only run them when the user explicitly asks for E2E testing.\\n    54→\\n    55→```bash\\n    56→mise run test:e2e [filter]                          # All agents, filtered\\n    57→mise run test:e2e --agent claude-code [filter]       # Claude Code only\\n    58→mise run test:e2e --agent gemini-cli [filter]        # Gemini CLI only\\n    59→mise run test:e2e --agent opencode [filter]          # OpenCode only\\n    60→```\\n    61→\\n    62→E2E tests:\\n    63→\\n    64→- Use the `//go:build e2e` build tag\\n    65→- Located in `e2e/tests/`\\n    66→- See [`e2e/README.md`](e2e/README.md) for full documentation (structure, debugging, adding agents)\\n    67→- Test real agent interactions (Claude Code, Gemini CLI, OpenCode, or Cursor creating files, committing, etc.)\\n    68→- Validate checkpoint scenarios documented in `docs/architecture/checkpoint-scenarios.md`\\n    69→- Support multiple agents via `E2E_AGENT` env var (`claude-code`, `gemini`, `opencode`, `cursor`)\\n    70→\\n    71→**Environment variables:**\\n    72→\\n    73→- `E2E_AGENT` - Agent to test with (default: `claude-code`)\\n    74→- `E2E_CLAUDE_MODEL` - Claude model to use (default: `haiku` for cost efficiency)\\n    75→- `E2E_TIMEOUT` - Timeout per prompt (default: `2m`)\\n    76→\\n    77→### Test Parallelization\\n    78→\\n    79→**Always use `t.Parallel()` in tests.** Every top-level test function and subtest should call `t.Parallel()` unless it modifies process-global state (e.g., `os.Chdir()`).\\n    80→\\n    81→```go\\n    82→func TestFeature_Foo(t *testing.T) {\\n    83→    t.Parallel()\\n    84→    // ...\\n    85→}\\n    86→\\n    87→// Integration tests with TestEnv\\n    88→func TestFeature_Bar(t *testing.T) {\\n    89→    t.Parallel()\\n    90→    env := NewFeatureBranchEnv(t)\\n    91→    // ...\\n    92→}\\n    93→```\\n    94→\\n    95→**Exception:** Tests that modify process-global state cannot be parallelized. This includes `os.Chdir()`/`t.Chdir()` and `os.Setenv()`/`t.Setenv()` — Go's test framework will panic if these are used after `t.Parallel()`.\\n    96→\\n    97→### Linting and Formatting\\n    98→\\n    99→```bash\\n   100→mise run fmt && mise run lint\\n   101→```\\n   102→\\n   103→### Before Every Commit (REQUIRED)\\n   104→\\n   105→**CI will fail if you skip these steps:**\\n   106→\\n   107→```bash\\n   108→mise run fmt      # Format code (CI enforces gofmt)\\n   109→mise run lint     # Lint check (CI enforces golangci-lint)\\n   110→mise run test:ci  # Run all tests (unit + integration)\\n   111→```\\n   112→\\n   113→Or combined: `mise run fmt && mise run lint && mise run test:ci`\\n   114→\\n   115→**Common CI failures from skipping this:**\\n   116→\\n   117→- `gofmt` formatting differences → run `mise run fmt`\\n   118→- Lint errors → run `mise run lint` and fix issues\\n   119→- Test failures → run `mise run test` and fix\\n   120→\\n   121→### Code Duplication Prevention\\n   122→\\n   123→Before implementing Go code, use `/go:discover-related` to find existing utilities and patterns that might be reusable.\\n   124→\\n   125→**Check for duplication:**\\n   126→\\n   127→```bash\\n   128→mise run dup           # Comprehensive check (threshold 50) with summary\\n   129→mise run dup:staged    # Check only staged files\\n   130→mise run lint          # Normal lint includes dupl at threshold 75 (new issues only)\\n   131→mise run lint:full     # All issues at threshold 75\\n   132→```\\n   133→\\n   134→**Tiered thresholds:**\\n   135→\\n   136→- **75 tokens** (lint/CI) - Blocks on serious duplication (~20+ lines)\\n   137→- **50 tokens** (dup) - Advisory, catches smaller patterns (~10+ lines)\\n   138→\\n   139→When duplication is found:\\n   140→\\n   141→1. Check if a helper already exists in `common.go` or nearby utility files\\n   142→2. If not, consider extracting the duplicated logic to a shared helper\\n   143→3. If duplication is intentional (e.g., test setup), add a `//nolint:dupl` comment with explanation\\n   144→\\n   145→## Code Patterns\\n   146→\\n   147→### Error Handling\\n   148→\\n   149→The CLI uses a specific pattern for error output to avoid duplication between Cobra and main.go.\\n   150→\\n   151→**How it works:**\\n   152→\\n   153→- `root.go` sets `SilenceErrors: true` globally - Cobra never prints errors\\n   154→- `main.go` prints errors to stderr, unless the error is a `SilentError`\\n   155→- Commands return `NewSilentError(err)` when they've already printed a custom message\\n   156→\\n   157→**When to use `SilentError`:**\\n   158→Use `NewSilentError()` when you want to print a custom, user-friendly error message instead of the raw error:\\n   159→\\n   160→```go\\n   161→// In a command's RunE function:\\n   162→if _, err := paths.WorktreeRoot(); err != nil {\\n   163→    cmd.SilenceUsage = true  // Don't show usage for prerequisite errors\\n   164→    fmt.Fprintln(cmd.ErrOrStderr(), \\\"Not a git repository. Please run 'entire enable' from within a git repository.\\\")\\n   165→    return NewSilentError(errors.New(\\\"not a git repository\\\"))\\n   166→}\\n   167→```\\n   168→\\n   169→**When NOT to use `SilentError`:**\\n   170→For normal errors where the default error message is sufficient, just return the error directly. main.go will print it:\\n   171→\\n   172→```go\\n   173→// Normal error - main.go will print \\\"unknown strategy: foo\\\"\\n   174→return fmt.Errorf(\\\"unknown strategy: %s\\\", name)\\n   175→```\\n   176→\\n   177→**Key files:**\\n   178→\\n   179→- `errors.go` - Defines `SilentError` type and `NewSilentError()` constructor\\n   180→- `root.go` - Sets `SilenceErrors: true` on root command\\n   181→- `main.go` - Checks for `SilentError` before printing\\n   182→\\n   183→### Settings\\n   184→\\n   185→All settings access should go through the `settings` package (`cmd/entire/cli/settings/`).\\n   186→\\n   187→**Why a separate package:**\\n   188→The `settings` package exists to avoid import cycles. The `cli` package imports `strategy`, so `strategy` cannot import `cli`. The `settings` package provides shared settings loading that both can use.\\n   189→\\n   190→**Usage:**\\n   191→\\n   192→```go\\n   193→import \\\"github.com/entireio/cli/cmd/entire/cli/settings\\\"\\n   194→\\n   195→// Load full settings object\\n   196→s, err := settings.Load()\\n   197→if err != nil {\\n   198→    // handle error\\n   199→}\\n   200→if s.Enabled {\"}]},\"uuid\":\"44927dda-9419-47ed-93bb-b186de912e3c\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-03-03T20:15:18.695Z\"},\"normalizedMessages\":[],\"type\":\"agent_progress\",\"prompt\":\"\",\"agentId\":\"a8b730080ffbc16fc\"},\"toolUseID\":\"agent_msg_01Hae6tBjtF6M39zkiWyFieq\",\"parentToolUseID\":\"toolu_019hgMuvwjnK2bzjd1zFXxE6\",\"uuid\":\"1d3db0e8-4e14-4fff-972b-9e8f1c44ce3d\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-03-03T20:15:18.768Z\"}\n{\"parentUuid\":\"1d3db0e8-4e14-4fff-972b-9e8f1c44ce3d\",\"isSidechain\":false,\"userType\":\"external\",\"cwd\":\"/Users/alisha/Projects/wt/kiro-oneshot\",\"sessionId\":\"f99ad6f8-76a8-4008-9fe1-81f1ba469547\",\"version\":\"2.1.63\",\"gitBranch\":\"alisha/kiro-oneshot\",\"slug\":\"glittery-waddling-parrot\",\"type\":\"progress\",\"data\":{\"message\":{\"type\":\"user\",\"message\":{\"role\":\"user\",\"content\":[{\"tool_use_id\":\"toolu_01G1i7s5jeg4tutPay14n1Lf\",\"type\":\"tool_result\",\"content\":\"     1→// hook_registry.go provides hook command registration for agents.\\n     2→// The lifecycle dispatcher (DispatchLifecycleEvent) handles all lifecycle events.\\n     3→// PostTodo is the only hook that's handled directly (not via lifecycle dispatcher).\\n     4→package cli\\n     5→\\n     6→import (\\n     7→\\t\\\"errors\\\"\\n     8→\\t\\\"fmt\\\"\\n     9→\\t\\\"log/slog\\\"\\n    10→\\t\\\"time\\\"\\n    11→\\n    12→\\t\\\"github.com/entireio/cli/cmd/entire/cli/agent\\\"\\n    13→\\t\\\"github.com/entireio/cli/cmd/entire/cli/agent/claudecode\\\"\\n    14→\\t\\\"github.com/entireio/cli/cmd/entire/cli/agent/geminicli\\\"\\n    15→\\t\\\"github.com/entireio/cli/cmd/entire/cli/agent/types\\\"\\n    16→\\t\\\"github.com/entireio/cli/cmd/entire/cli/logging\\\"\\n    17→\\t\\\"github.com/entireio/cli/cmd/entire/cli/paths\\\"\\n    18→\\t\\\"github.com/entireio/cli/cmd/entire/cli/strategy\\\"\\n    19→\\n    20→\\t\\\"github.com/spf13/cobra\\\"\\n    21→)\\n    22→\\n    23→// agentHookLogCleanup stores the cleanup function for agent hook logging.\\n    24→// Set by PersistentPreRunE, called by PersistentPostRunE.\\n    25→var agentHookLogCleanup func()\\n    26→\\n    27→// currentHookAgentName stores the agent name for the currently executing hook.\\n    28→// Set by newAgentHookVerbCmdWithLogging before calling the handler.\\n    29→// This allows handlers to know which agent invoked the hook without guessing.\\n    30→var currentHookAgentName types.AgentName\\n    31→\\n    32→// GetCurrentHookAgent returns the agent for the currently executing hook.\\n    33→// Returns the agent based on the hook command structure (e.g., \\\"entire hooks claude-code ...\\\")\\n    34→// rather than guessing from directory presence.\\n    35→// Falls back to GetAgent() if not in a hook context.\\n    36→func GetCurrentHookAgent() (agent.Agent, error) {\\n    37→\\tif currentHookAgentName == \\\"\\\" {\\n    38→\\t\\treturn nil, errors.New(\\\"not in a hook context: agent name not set\\\")\\n    39→\\t}\\n    40→\\n    41→\\tag, err := agent.Get(currentHookAgentName)\\n    42→\\tif err != nil {\\n    43→\\t\\treturn nil, fmt.Errorf(\\\"getting hook agent %q: %w\\\", currentHookAgentName, err)\\n    44→\\t}\\n    45→\\treturn ag, nil\\n    46→}\\n    47→\\n    48→// newAgentHooksCmd creates a hooks subcommand for an agent that implements HookSupport.\\n    49→// It dynamically creates subcommands for each hook the agent supports.\\n    50→func newAgentHooksCmd(agentName types.AgentName, handler agent.HookSupport) *cobra.Command {\\n    51→\\tcmd := &cobra.Command{\\n    52→\\t\\tUse:    string(agentName),\\n    53→\\t\\tShort:  handler.Description() + \\\" hook handlers\\\",\\n    54→\\t\\tHidden: true,\\n    55→\\t\\tPersistentPreRunE: func(cmd *cobra.Command, _ []string) error {\\n    56→\\t\\t\\tagentHookLogCleanup = initHookLogging(cmd.Context())\\n    57→\\t\\t\\treturn nil\\n    58→\\t\\t},\\n    59→\\t\\tPersistentPostRunE: func(_ *cobra.Command, _ []string) error {\\n    60→\\t\\t\\tif agentHookLogCleanup != nil {\\n    61→\\t\\t\\t\\tagentHookLogCleanup()\\n    62→\\t\\t\\t}\\n    63→\\t\\t\\treturn nil\\n    64→\\t\\t},\\n    65→\\t}\\n    66→\\n    67→\\tfor _, hookName := range handler.HookNames() {\\n    68→\\t\\tcmd.AddCommand(newAgentHookVerbCmdWithLogging(agentName, hookName))\\n    69→\\t}\\n    70→\\n    71→\\treturn cmd\\n    72→}\\n    73→\\n    74→// getHookType returns the hook type based on the hook name.\\n    75→// Returns \\\"subagent\\\" for task-related hooks (pre-task, post-task, post-todo),\\n    76→// \\\"tool\\\" for tool-related hooks (before-tool, after-tool),\\n    77→// \\\"agent\\\" for all other agent hooks.\\n    78→func getHookType(hookName string) string {\\n    79→\\tswitch hookName {\\n    80→\\tcase claudecode.HookNamePreTask, claudecode.HookNamePostTask, claudecode.HookNamePostTodo:\\n    81→\\t\\treturn \\\"subagent\\\"\\n    82→\\tcase geminicli.HookNameBeforeTool, geminicli.HookNameAfterTool:\\n    83→\\t\\treturn \\\"tool\\\"\\n    84→\\tdefault:\\n    85→\\t\\treturn \\\"agent\\\"\\n    86→\\t}\\n    87→}\\n    88→\\n    89→// newAgentHookVerbCmdWithLogging creates a command for a specific hook verb with structured logging.\\n    90→// It uses the lifecycle dispatcher (ParseHookEvent → DispatchLifecycleEvent) as the primary path.\\n    91→// PostTodo is handled directly as it's Claude-specific and not part of the lifecycle dispatcher.\\n    92→func newAgentHookVerbCmdWithLogging(agentName types.AgentName, hookName string) *cobra.Command {\\n    93→\\treturn &cobra.Command{\\n    94→\\t\\tUse:    hookName,\\n    95→\\t\\tHidden: true,\\n    96→\\t\\tShort:  \\\"Called on \\\" + hookName,\\n    97→\\t\\tRunE: func(cmd *cobra.Command, _ []string) error {\\n    98→\\t\\t\\t// Skip silently if not in a git repository - hooks shouldn't prevent the agent from working\\n    99→\\t\\t\\tif _, err := paths.WorktreeRoot(cmd.Context()); err != nil {\\n   100→\\t\\t\\t\\treturn nil\\n   101→\\t\\t\\t}\\n   102→\\n   103→\\t\\t\\t// Skip if Entire is not enabled\\n   104→\\t\\t\\tenabled, err := IsEnabled(cmd.Context())\\n   105→\\t\\t\\tif err == nil && !enabled {\\n   106→\\t\\t\\t\\treturn nil\\n   107→\\t\\t\\t}\\n   108→\\n   109→\\t\\t\\tstart := time.Now()\\n   110→\\n   111→\\t\\t\\t// Initialize logging context with agent name\\n   112→\\t\\t\\tctx := logging.WithAgent(logging.WithComponent(cmd.Context(), \\\"hooks\\\"), agentName)\\n   113→\\n   114→\\t\\t\\t// Strategy name for logging\\n   115→\\t\\t\\tstrategyName := strategy.StrategyNameManualCommit\\n   116→\\n   117→\\t\\t\\thookType := getHookType(hookName)\\n   118→\\n   119→\\t\\t\\tlogging.Debug(ctx, \\\"hook invoked\\\",\\n   120→\\t\\t\\t\\tslog.String(\\\"hook\\\", hookName),\\n   121→\\t\\t\\t\\tslog.String(\\\"hook_type\\\", hookType),\\n   122→\\t\\t\\t\\tslog.String(\\\"strategy\\\", strategyName),\\n   123→\\t\\t\\t)\\n   124→\\n   125→\\t\\t\\t// Set the current hook agent so handlers can retrieve it\\n   126→\\t\\t\\tcurrentHookAgentName = agentName\\n   127→\\t\\t\\tdefer func() { currentHookAgentName = \\\"\\\" }()\\n   128→\\n   129→\\t\\t\\t// Use the lifecycle dispatcher for all hooks\\n   130→\\t\\t\\tvar hookErr error\\n   131→\\t\\t\\tag, agentErr := agent.Get(agentName)\\n   132→\\t\\t\\tif agentErr != nil {\\n   133→\\t\\t\\t\\treturn fmt.Errorf(\\\"failed to get agent %q: %w\\\", agentName, agentErr)\\n   134→\\t\\t\\t}\\n   135→\\n   136→\\t\\t\\thandler, ok := ag.(agent.HookSupport)\\n   137→\\t\\t\\tif !ok {\\n   138→\\t\\t\\t\\treturn fmt.Errorf(\\\"agent %q does not support hooks\\\", agentName)\\n   139→\\t\\t\\t}\\n   140→\\n   141→\\t\\t\\t// Use cmd.InOrStdin() to support testing with cmd.SetIn()\\n   142→\\t\\t\\tevent, parseErr := handler.ParseHookEvent(ctx, hookName, cmd.InOrStdin())\\n   143→\\t\\t\\tif parseErr != nil {\\n   144→\\t\\t\\t\\treturn fmt.Errorf(\\\"failed to parse hook event: %w\\\", parseErr)\\n   145→\\t\\t\\t}\\n   146→\\n   147→\\t\\t\\tif event != nil {\\n   148→\\t\\t\\t\\t// Lifecycle event — use the generic dispatcher\\n   149→\\t\\t\\t\\thookErr = DispatchLifecycleEvent(ctx, ag, event)\\n   150→\\t\\t\\t} else if agentName == agent.AgentNameClaudeCode && hookName == claudecode.HookNamePostTodo {\\n   151→\\t\\t\\t\\t// PostTodo is Claude-specific: creates incremental checkpoints during subagent execution\\n   152→\\t\\t\\t\\thookErr = handleClaudeCodePostTodo(ctx)\\n   153→\\t\\t\\t}\\n   154→\\t\\t\\t// Other pass-through hooks (nil event, no special handling) are no-ops\\n   155→\\n   156→\\t\\t\\tlogging.LogDuration(ctx, slog.LevelDebug, \\\"hook completed\\\", start,\\n   157→\\t\\t\\t\\tslog.String(\\\"hook\\\", hookName),\\n   158→\\t\\t\\t\\tslog.String(\\\"hook_type\\\", hookType),\\n   159→\\t\\t\\t\\tslog.String(\\\"strategy\\\", strategyName),\\n   160→\\t\\t\\t\\tslog.Bool(\\\"success\\\", hookErr == nil),\\n   161→\\t\\t\\t)\\n   162→\\n   163→\\t\\t\\treturn hookErr\\n   164→\\t\\t},\\n   165→\\t}\\n   166→}\\n   167→\"}]},\"uuid\":\"1f2e52c6-dbf5-4417-8522-9b8eead45a05\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-03-03T20:15:18.783Z\"},\"normalizedMessages\":[],\"type\":\"agent_progress\",\"prompt\":\"\",\"agentId\":\"ad3c9b2e11cd3a9aa\"},\"toolUseID\":\"agent_msg_01Hae6tBjtF6M39zkiWyFieq\",\"parentToolUseID\":\"toolu_01Qf7tecwL49faBn75P6zcYS\",\"uuid\":\"cf8bbb7c-e391-4c8b-8d22-c946e74ce682\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-03-03T20:15:18.852Z\"}\n{\"parentUuid\":\"cf8bbb7c-e391-4c8b-8d22-c946e74ce682\",\"isSidechain\":false,\"userType\":\"external\",\"cwd\":\"/Users/alisha/Projects/wt/kiro-oneshot\",\"sessionId\":\"f99ad6f8-76a8-4008-9fe1-81f1ba469547\",\"version\":\"2.1.63\",\"gitBranch\":\"alisha/kiro-oneshot\",\"slug\":\"glittery-waddling-parrot\",\"type\":\"progress\",\"data\":{\"message\":{\"type\":\"assistant\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-03-03T20:15:18.918Z\",\"message\":{\"model\":\"claude-haiku-4-5-20251001\",\"id\":\"msg_01ADKcHSWM6DkHf1yU1svVAk\",\"type\":\"message\",\"role\":\"assistant\",\"content\":[{\"type\":\"tool_use\",\"id\":\"toolu_01NVZ9Fj6BKi5Q2Faii5rMRj\",\"name\":\"Read\",\"input\":{\"file_path\":\"/Users/alisha/Projects/wt/kiro-oneshot/cmd/entire/cli/lifecycle.go\"},\"caller\":{\"type