en by linter).\",\"-\",\"-### 4. `cmd/entire/cli/agent/kiro/hooks_test.go` — Update and add tests\",\"-\",\"-**Updated existing tests** (count changes from 5 → 9):\",\"-- `TestInstallHooks_FreshInstall`: expect count 9\",\"-- `TestInstallHooks_LocalDevMode`: expect count 9\",\"-- `TestInstallHooks_Idempotent`: first count = 9\",\"-- `TestInstallHooks_ForceReinstall`: expect count 9\",\"-- `TestInstallHooks_CountMatchesHookNames`: update to assert `count == len(ag.HookNames()) + len(ideHookDefs)`\",\"-\",\"-**New tests:**\",\"-- `TestInstallHooks_CreatesIDEHookFiles` — verify all 4 files exist\",\"-- `TestInstallHooks_IDEHooksValidJSON` — verify JSON structure, enabled, version, when.type, then.type, command\",\"-- `TestInstallHooks_IDEHooksLocalDevMode` — verify local dev command prefix\",\"-- `TestInstallHooks_IDEHooksFilePermissions` — verify 0600\",\"-- `TestInstallHooks_IDEHooksAllTriggerTypes` — verify each file has correct when.type\",\"-- `TestUninstallHooks_RemovesIDEHookFiles` — verify cleanup\",\"-- `TestAreHooksInstalled_IDEOnlyHooks` — verify detection without CLI agent file\",\"-- `TestInstallHooks_Idempotent_IncludesIDEHooks` — verify combined idempotency\",\"-\",\"-### 5. `cmd/entire/cli/agent/kiro/lifecycle_test.go` — Update empty-stdin tests\",\"-\",\"-**Updated existing tests** (empty stdin now succeeds instead of erroring):\",\"-- `TestParseHookEvent_EmptyInput`: change to expect success (SessionStart event)\",\"-- `TestParseHookEvent_EmptyInput_UserPromptSubmit`: change to expect success (TurnStart event)\",\"-- `TestParseHookEvent_EmptyInput_Stop`: change to expect success (TurnEnd event)\",\"-\",\"-**New tests:**\",\"-- `TestParseHookEvent_UserPromptSubmit_EmptyStdin_ReadsEnvVar` — verify `USER_PROMPT` env var fallback\",\"-- `TestParseHookEvent_Stop_EmptyStdin_Succeeds` — verify stop works with empty stdin + mock DB\",\"-\",\"-### 6. `cmd/entire/cli/agent/kiro/AGENT.md` — Update docs\",\"-\",\"-Add \\\"IDE Hook Configuration\\\" section documenting:\",\"-- `.kiro/hooks/` directory and file format\",\"-- The 4 IDE hook files installed\",\"-- Stdin vs environment variable data delivery difference\",\"-- No agentSpawn IDE trigger\",\"-\",\" ## Verification\",\" \",\" ```bash\",\" mise run fmt && mise run lint && mise run test:ci\",\" ```\",\" \",\"-Specific test commands:\",\"-```bash\",\"-go test ./cmd/entire/cli/agent/kiro/... -v -run \\\"TestInstallHooks|TestUninstallHooks|TestAreHooksInstalled\\\"\",\"-go test ./cmd/entire/cli/agent/kiro/... -v -run \\\"TestParseHookEvent_EmptyInput|TestParseHookEvent.*EmptyStdin\\\"\",\"-```\",\"+After deploying: run `entire enable --force` in the test repo to regenerate the hook files, then verify the IDE hooks fire by chatting in the Kiro IDE.\"]}],\"originalFile\":\"# Plan: Add Kiro IDE Hooks (.kiro/hooks/*.kiro.hook)\\n\\n## Context\\n\\nThe Kiro agent currently installs hooks only in `.kiro/agents/entire.json` (CLI agent definition format). This works for `kiro-cli chat --agent entire` but **not** for the Kiro IDE (VS Code extension), which reads hooks from `.kiro/hooks/*.kiro.hook` files. We need to install IDE hooks there while keeping the existing CLI agent hooks.\\n\\nKey difference: CLI hooks receive JSON on stdin. IDE hooks pass data via environment variables (`USER_PROMPT` for promptSubmit) with **no stdin**. The lifecycle parsers must handle empty stdin gracefully.\\n\\n## Changes\\n\\n### 1. `cmd/entire/cli/agent/kiro/types.go` — Add IDE hook types\\n\\nAdd 3 structs for the `.kiro.hook` file format:\\n\\n```go\\ntype kiroIDEHookFile struct {\\n    Enabled     bool            `json:\\\"enabled\\\"`\\n    Name        string          `json:\\\"name\\\"`\\n    Description string          `json:\\\"description\\\"`\\n    Version     string          `json:\\\"version\\\"`\\n    When        kiroIDEHookWhen `json:\\\"when\\\"`\\n    Then        kiroIDEHookThen `json:\\\"then\\\"`\\n}\\n\\ntype kiroIDEHookWhen struct {\\n    Type string `json:\\\"type\\\"`\\n}\\n\\ntype kiroIDEHookThen struct {\\n    Type    string `json:\\\"type\\\"`\\n    Command string `json:\\\"command\\\"`\\n}\\n```\\n\\n### 2. `cmd/entire/cli/agent/kiro/hooks.go` — Install/uninstall/check IDE hooks\\n\\n**New constants and data:**\\n- `ideHooksDir = \\\"hooks\\\"` — directory within `.kiro`\\n- `ideHookFileSuffix = \\\".kiro.hook\\\"`\\n- `ideHookDefs` — slice of 4 definitions mapping filename → trigger type → CLI verb\\n\\n**IDE hooks to install (4 files):**\\n\\n| File | `when.type` | Command |\\n|------|-------------|---------|\\n| `entire-prompt-submit.kiro.hook` | `promptSubmit` | `entire hooks kiro user-prompt-submit` |\\n| `entire-stop.kiro.hook` | `agentStop` | `entire hooks kiro stop` |\\n| `entire-pre-tool-use.kiro.hook` | `preToolUse` | `entire hooks kiro pre-tool-use` |\\n| `entire-post-tool-use.kiro.hook` | `postToolUse` | `entire hooks kiro post-tool-use` |\\n\\nNo `agentSpawn` IDE hook (no IDE trigger exists). First `promptSubmit` serves as session start.\\n\\n**Modified functions:**\\n- `InstallHooks`: After writing CLI agent file, also call `installIDEHooks()` to create 4 `.kiro.hook` files. Idempotency gate checks both CLI and IDE hooks. Returns 9 on fresh install (5 CLI + 4 IDE).\\n- `UninstallHooks`: Also remove the 4 IDE hook files (idempotent, no error if missing).\\n- `AreHooksInstalled`: Also check for IDE hook files — returns true if EITHER CLI or IDE hooks are present.\\n\\n**New helpers:**\\n- `installIDEHooks(worktreeRoot, cmdPrefix) (int, error)` — creates `.kiro/hooks/` dir and writes 4 files\\n- `allIDEHooksPresent(worktreeRoot string, localDev bool) bool` — checks all 4 IDE hook files exist and have correct commands\\n- `isEntireIDEHook(hook kiroIDEHookFile) bool` — checks if IDE hook belongs to Entire\\n\\n### 3. `cmd/entire/cli/agent/kiro/lifecycle.go` — Handle empty stdin (IDE mode)\\n\\nAdd a local helper `readHookInputOrEmpty(stdin)` that wraps `ReadAndParseHookInput` and returns a zero-value `hookInputRaw{}` on empty stdin (instead of erroring). Malformed JSON still returns errors.\\n\\n**Modified parsers:**\\n- `parseAgentSpawn`: Use `readHookInputOrEmpty`. Empty stdin is fine — just generates session ID.\\n- `parseUserPromptSubmit`: Use `readHookInputOrEmpty`. If `raw.Prompt` is empty, read `os.Getenv(\\\"USER_PROMPT\\\")`. If `raw.CWD` is empty, use `paths.WorktreeRoot(ctx)`.\\n- `parseStop`: Use `readHookInputOrEmpty`. If `raw.CWD` is empty, use `paths.WorktreeRoot(ctx)`.\\n\\nNote: `paths.WorktreeRoot(ctx)` used for CWD fallback (not `os.Getwd()` which is forbidden by linter).\\n\\n### 4. `cmd/entire/cli/agent/kiro/hooks_test.go` — Update and add tests\\n\\n**Updated existing tests** (count changes from 5 → 9):\\n- `TestInstallHooks_FreshInstall`: expect count 9\\n- `TestInstallHooks_LocalDevMode`: expect count 9\\n- `TestInstallHooks_Idempotent`: first count = 9\\n- `TestInstallHooks_ForceReinstall`: expect count 9\\n- `TestInstallHooks_CountMatchesHookNames`: update to assert `count == len(ag.HookNames()) + len(ideHookDefs)`\\n\\n**New tests:**\\n- `TestInstallHooks_CreatesIDEHookFiles` — verify all 4 files exist\\n- `TestInstallHooks_IDEHooksValidJSON` — verify JSON structure, enabled, version, when.type, then.type, command\\n- `TestInstallHooks_IDEHooksLocalDevMode` — verify local dev command prefix\\n- `TestInstallHooks_IDEHooksFilePermissions` — verify 0600\\n- `TestInstallHooks_IDEHooksAllTriggerTypes` — verify each file has correct when.type\\n- `TestUninstallHooks_RemovesIDEHookFiles` — verify cleanup\\n- `TestAreHooksInstalled_IDEOnlyHooks` — verify detection without CLI agent file\\n- `TestInstallHooks_Idempotent_IncludesIDEHooks` — verify combined idempotency\\n\\n### 5. `cmd/entire/cli/agent/kiro/lifecycle_test.go` — Update empty-stdin tests\\n\\n**Updated existing tests** (empty stdin now succeeds instead of erroring):\\n- `TestParseHookEvent_EmptyInput`: change to expect success (SessionStart event)\\n- `TestParseHookEvent_EmptyInput_UserPromptSubmit`: change to expect success (TurnStart event)\\n- `TestParseHookEvent_EmptyInput_Stop`: change to expect success (TurnEnd event)\\n\\n**New tests:**\\n- `TestParseHookEvent_UserPromptSubmit_EmptyStdin_ReadsEnvVar` — verify `USER_PROMPT` env var fallback\\n- `TestParseHookEvent_Stop_EmptyStdin_Succeeds` — verify stop works with empty stdin + mock DB\\n\\n### 6. `cmd/entire/cli/agent/kiro/AGENT.md` — Update docs\\n\\nAdd \\\"IDE Hook Configuration\\\" section documenting:\\n- `.kiro/hooks/` directory and file format\\n- The 4 IDE hook files installed\\n- Stdin vs environment variable data delivery difference\\n- No agentSpawn IDE trigger\\n\\n## Verification\\n\\n```bash\\nmise run fmt && mise run lint && mise run test:ci\\n```\\n\\nSpecific test commands:\\n```bash\\ngo test ./cmd/entire/cli/agent/kiro/... -v -run \\\"TestInstallHooks|TestUninstallHooks|TestAreHooksInstalled\\\"\\ngo test ./cmd/entire/cli/agent/kiro/... -v -run \\\"TestParseHookEvent_EmptyInput|TestParseHookEvent.*EmptyStdin\\\"\\n```\\n\"},\"sourceToolAssistantUUID\":\"47566fa2-c9e6-4aca-ac8c-58085514ff0e\"}\n{\"parentUuid\":\"ad404060-8aef-4d25-82f9-99c1342cefeb\",\"isSidechain\":false,\"userType\":\"external\",\"cwd\":\"/Users/alisha/Projects/wt/kiro-oneshot\",\"sessionId\":\"f99ad6f8-76a8-4008-9fe1-81f1ba469547\",\"version\":\"2.1.63\",\"gitBranch\":\"alisha/kiro-oneshot\",\"slug\":\"glittery-waddling-parrot\",\"message\":{\"model\":\"claude-opus-4-6\",\"id\":\"msg_01MXCNk7tuZ5s4VBgQ8ixmgJ\",\"type\":\"message\",\"role\":\"assistant\",\"content\":[{\"type\":\"tool_use\",\"id\":\"toolu_01NZwiQs2s5tPUPySoqPJpfY\",\"name\":\"ExitPlanMode\",\"input\":{\"plan\":\"# Plan: Fix Kiro IDE Hook `then.type` — `\\\"command\\\"` → `\\\"runCommand\\\"`\\n\\n## Context\\n\\nThe Kiro IDE hooks installed by `entire enable` silently fail because `then.type` is set to `\\\"command\\\"`, but the Kiro IDE expects `\\\"runCommand\\\"`. The IDE ignores hooks with unrecognized action types without logging any error — which is why there are no logs in `.entire/`.\\n\\n**Root cause (from comparing working vs broken hook):**\\n```\\nBroken (ours):   \\\"then\\\": { \\\"type\\\": \\\"command\\\",    \\\"command\\\": \\\"entire hooks kiro ...\\\" }\\nWorking (manual): \\\"then\\\": { \\\"type\\\": \\\"runCommand\\\", \\\"command\\\": \\\"ls -a\\\" }\\n```\\n\\n## Changes\\n\\n### 1. `cmd/entire/cli/agent/kiro/hooks.go` — Fix the action type constant\\n\\nIn `installIDEHooks()`, change `Type: \\\"command\\\"` → `Type: \\\"runCommand\\\"`:\\n\\n```go\\n// Before:\\nThen: kiroIDEHookThen{\\n    Type:    \\\"command\\\",          // ← WRONG\\n    Command: cmdPrefix + def.CLIVerb,\\n},\\n\\n// After:\\nThen: kiroIDEHookThen{\\n    Type:    \\\"runCommand\\\",       // ← CORRECT\\n    Command: cmdPrefix + def.CLIVerb,\\n},\\n```\\n\\n### 2. `cmd/entire/cli/agent/kiro/hooks_test.go` — Update test assertion\\n\\nIn `TestInstallHooks_IDEHooksValidJSON`, update the assertion:\\n```go\\n// Before:\\nif hook.Then.Type != \\\"command\\\" {\\n\\n// After:\\nif hook.Then.Type != \\\"runCommand\\\" {\\n```\\n\\n### 3. `cmd/entire/cli/agent/kiro/AGENT.md` — Fix documented format\\n\\nUpdate the example JSON in the \\\"IDE Hook Configuration\\\" section:\\n```json\\n\\\"then\\\": {\\n    \\\"type\\\": \\\"runCommand\\\",\\n    \\\"command\\\": \\\"entire hooks kiro user-prompt-submit\\\"\\n}\\n```\\n\\n## Files Modified\\n\\n- `cmd/entire/cli/agent/kiro/hooks.go` (1 line)\\n- `cmd/entire/cli/agent/kiro/hooks_test.go` (1 line)\\n- `cmd/entire/cli/agent/kiro/AGENT.md` (1 line in example)\\n\\n## Verification\\n\\n```bash\\nmise run fmt && mise run lint && mise run test:ci\\n```\\n\\nAfter deploying: run `entire enable --force` in the test repo to regenerate the hook files, then verify the IDE hooks fire by chatting in the Kiro IDE.\\n\"},\"caller\":{\"type\":\"direct\"}}],\"stop_reason\":\"tool_use\",\"stop_sequence\":null,\"usage\":{\"input_tokens\":1,\"cache_creation_input_tokens\":1391,\"cache_read_input_tok